-Mgu_a4nyaouANvVXY3v.text: Citizen user video shows a police unit at the scene of an unspecified incident.

nib.text:
Minneapolis police arrested a suspect after the fatal stabbing of a man in Loring Park Thursday morning.

At about 6:14 a.m., officers responded to a report of a stabbing at an address on the 300 block of Oak Grove Street.

On the upper floor of a building, officers located the victim suffering from wounds apparently from a straight-edge weapon.

The victim was rushed to an area hospital, but died a short time later.

Police said that officers developed a lead and arrested the suspect, described as an adult male.

He was transported to the homicide unit for an interview.

Police also recovered a weapon at the scene.

Additional information will be released from the Medical Examiner’s Office.

Anyone with information is urged to contact CrimeStoppers at 800-222-8477.
